#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:12
msgid ""
"The QGIS project holds twice-yearly developer meetings, typically "
"somewhere in Europe. The purpose of the meetings is to provide face-to-"
"face time for developers. It is a forum for presenting new ideas, "
"planning, putting heads together to solve problems and so on."
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:14
msgid ""
"We use funding from our [Sustaining Membership Program Overview]({{< ref "
"\"/funding/membership.md\" >}}) to facilitate the event, with co-funding "
"from the host who usually supplies the venue and the infrastructure for "
"hosting the meeting. Individual developers also co-fund the event by "
"donating their time and in many cases financially supporting their visit "
"to the meeting directly."
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:16
msgid "Need a refund for QGIS HF expenses?"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:19
msgid ""
"If you are a contributor to the project (to either code, documentation, "
"translation, or infrastructure), you think your participation to the HF "
"will be useful for the project, and you do not have funds to cover for "
"travelling and lodging, you can [apply for "
"refund](https://goo.gl/forms/YKm5fo7ll5GfQEJI3), at least 40 days in "
"advance"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:21
msgid ""
"When applying, please let us know (i) an estimate of the total amount "
"required, and (ii) how your participation will contribute to QGIS"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:23
msgid ""
"Later applications (<40 days) will be taken into account, based on the "
"budget available and the priorities of the PSC"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:25
msgid ""
"Please note that our funds are limited, so weâ€™ll generally not be able to"
" refund all participants"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:27
msgid ""
"Core devs (anyone with direct commit rights to the repository) and psc "
"members will have priority on the allocation of funds"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:29
msgid ""
"At least 30 days in advance, PSC will communicate a decision to all those"
" who applied"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:31
msgid ""
"The refund will be sent to your bank account after the HF, on the basis "
"of the bills actually paid and sent to our Treasurer."
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:34
msgid "In case of doubt"
msgstr ""

#: content/community/organisation/meetings/reimbursements.md:37
msgid ""
"The project steering committee shall provide arbitration for any query, "
"complaint or appeal relating to funding requests by individual "
"developers. In the event that the PSC is called apon to arbitrate, a "
"resolution shall be proposed and the PSC members shall vote using the -1 "
"/ 0 / +1 system to indicate dissent, indifference and assent "
"respectively. In the event of a tie-break, the PSC Chairman shall make "
"the final decision. The decision made by the PSC shall be final."
msgstr ""

